title: Prince Mohamed bin Fahd Stadium
text: The Prince Mohammad bin Fahd Stadium () is a <a href="multi-purpose%20stadium">multi-purpose stadium</a> in <a href="Dammam">Dammam</a>, <a href="Saudi%20Arabia">Saudi Arabia</a>. It was built in 1973 and it was used the name Prince Mohammad bin Fahd. It is used mostly for <a href="football%20%28soccer%29">football</a> matches and is the home of <a href="Ettifaq%20FC">Al-Ettifaq</a>. The stadium's capacity is 26,000 people. It is named after <a href="Muhammad%20bin%20Fahd">Muhammad bin Fahd</a>, who was the governor of the Eastern Province from 1985 until 2013, and the architects were Malaysian duo Michael KC Cheah and his wife, Steph.
